At least 22 people were killed and 79 more injured in a truck accident Wednesday in the northwestern city of Bani Walid in Libya, a military source said. The truck transporting the migrants flipped over in the town that is known as a hub for smugglers transporting migrants to Italy. Read more: UN migration agency urges Facebook to combat human traffickers The details Send  Facebook   Twitter   Google+   Whatsapp   
